news.news: Siakam provided 19 points (7-16 FG, 0-3 3Pt, 5-5 FT), six rebounds and two assists in 24 minutes during Monday's 113-99 victory over Brooklyn.
news.analysis: Siakam reached the 15-point plateau for the fifth straight game, but that's the only noteworthy outcome of his performance. He's recorded just one double-double in that span. Siakam is averaging 17.8 points, 8.2 rebounds and 4.0 assists per game over that five-game stretch, but even if his numbers are a bit down compared to his regular-season averages, he should remain a reliable offensive weapon for the Pacers going forward.
